Cosmology|cTopic=Key topics

The Big Bang Scientific theory|theory is the prevailing Physical cosmology|cosmological Scientific modelling|model for the observable universe<ref name="NYT-20170220">cite news |last=Overbye |first=Dennis |authorlink=Dennis Overbye |title=Cosmos Controversy: The Universe Is Expanding, but How Fast? |newspaper=The New York Times |date=20 February 2017 |url=
https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/20/science/hubble-constant-universe-expanding-speed.html |accessdate=21 February 2017</ref><ref>cite article |last=Kurki-Suonio |first=Hannu |title=Cosmology I |page=9-10 |publisher=University of Helsinki |year=2018 |url=http://www.helsinki.fi/~hkurkisu/cosmology/Cosm1.pdf |accessdate=30 January 2019</ref><ref>cite article |last=Kornreich |first=Dave |title=Can we find the place where the Big Bang happened? (Intermediate) |publisher=Ask an Astronomer, Cornell University |date=27 June 2015 |url=http://curious.astro.cornell.edu/about-us/102-the-universe/cosmology-and-the-big-bang/the-big-bang/592-can-we-find-the-place-where-the-big-bang-happened-intermediate |accessdate=20 October 2018</ref> from the Planck units#Cosmology|earliest known periods through its subsequent large-scale evolution.<ref>cite book |last=Silk |first=Joseph |authorlink=Joseph Silk |title=Horizons of Cosmology |page=208 |publisher=John Templeton Foundation|Templeton Press |year=2009</ref><ref>cite book |last=Singh |first=Simon |authorlink=Simon Singh |title=Big Bang: The Origin of the Universe |page=560 |publisher=Harper Perennial |year=2005</ref><ref>cite web
 |last=Wollack 
 |first=Edward J. 
 |title=Cosmology: The Study of the Universe 
 |work=Universe 101: Big Bang Theory 
 |publisher=NASA 
 |date=10 December 2010 
 |url=http://map.gsfc.nasa.gov/universe/ 
